ingredients: ["2 bars (4 oz. each) German sweet chocolate", "1 Tbsp. butter", "2 eggs", "3/4 c. sugar", "1/4 c. unsifted flour", "1/4 tsp. baking powder", "1/8 tsp. salt", "1/4 tsp. cinnamon", "1/2 tsp. vanilla", "3/4 c. finely chopped pecans"]
directions: ["Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.", "Stir to blend; cool.", "Beat eggs until foamy.", "Add sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, beating until thickened, about 5 minutes with mixer.", "Blend in chocolate mixture.", "Add flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; blend.", "Stir in vanilla and pecans.", "Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.", "Bake in moderate oven (350\u00b0) until cookies feel set when lightly touched, 8 to 10 minutes.", "Store in tightly covered container.", "Makes about 36 cookies."]

title: Italian-Style Broccoli
ingredients: ["1 1/2 lb. fresh broccoli", "1/4 c. olive oil", "2 cloves garlic, minced", "2 Tbsp. lemon juice", "1/4 tsp. grated lemon rind", "lemon slices (optional)"]
directions: ["Trim", "off", "large leaves of broccoli.", "Remove tough ends to lower", "stalks; cut up and mix with other ingredients.", "Put in baking dish and bake uncovered in 350\u00b0 oven for 25 minutes or until tender.", "Garnish with lemon slices if desired."]
